.TH "platform_device_del" 9 "platform_device_del" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
platform_device_del \- remove a platform-level device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" platform_device_del
.BI "(struct platform_device *pdev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
platform device we're removing
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Note that this function will also release all memory- and port-based
resources owned by the device (\fIdev->resource\fP).  This function must
_only_ be externally called in error cases.  All other usage is a bug.
